## Code Style & Formatting
- Use TypeScript for all new code
- No usage of 'any' type
- Resist usage of casting when possible
- Use meaningful variable and function names with a preference for explicit longer names if necessary
- Add JSDoc comments for all APIs and important functions
- Prefer functional components when possible
- Write Unit tests for all important functions

## UI
- Mobile first web design
- Always reach for a shadcn component when available
- Keep everything as simple and vanilla shadncn as possible.

## Project Structure
- Keep components in `/components` directory
- Store utilities in `/utils` directory
- Place types/interfaces in `/types` directory
- Place documentation md files in `/docs` directory
- Place scratch md files in root directory
- Use index files for clean imports

## Final Notes
- Above all else, keep it simple
